==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loggia
<hw>Log"gia</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. See
<er>Lodge</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A roofed open gallery. It
differs from a <contr>veranda</contr> in being more architectural, and
in forming more decidedly a part of the main edifice to which it is
attached; from a <contr>porch</contr>, in being intended not for
entrance but for an out-of-door sitting-room.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Logging</ent>⟦br⟧
